parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission jerks or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Axle and hub bearing failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes
the axle or hub bearing makes unusual noises
the vehicle pulls to one side
the axle or hub bearing overheats.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: PCM failure can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift erratically, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle's engine light comes on
the vehicle's performance is poor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission shifting issues can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the transmission hesitates or jerks when shifting
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Steering and wheel vibration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes
the steering wheel vibrates or pulls to one side
the vehicle's tires wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The "death wobble" can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Violent front-end vibration or shaking
often occurring between 40-60 mph
which can be triggered by hitting a bump or rough road surface. The vibration can be intense
causing the steering wheel and front end to shake violently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ball joint failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of control
vibration
or shaking of the front end
often accompanied by a loud noise.
